# Fix broken table widget in `dashboard view`

## Problem

The table widgets ("Top Users", "Top Orgs", "By Country") in `dashboard view` render raw markdown pipe syntax (`| HEADER | HEADER |`, `| --- | --- |`, `| val | val |`) instead of properly formatted aligned text.

**Root cause**: `renderTableContent()` at `src/lib/formatters/dashboard.ts:782-805` uses `mdTableHeader()` and `mdRow()` from `markdown.ts` to produce CommonMark pipe table syntax. These raw strings are placed directly into the widget border box via `wrapInBorder()` without ever being passed through `renderMarkdown()`. The result is literal pipe characters visible in the terminal.

Additionally, `mdTableHeader()` returns a string with an embedded `\n` (header + separator as one string), which gets treated as a single line by `buildBorderedLine()`, further corrupting the display.

## Fix

### 1. Rewrite `renderTableContent()` (dashboard.ts:782-805)

Replace the markdown pipe table approach with direct aligned-text rendering:

- Accept `innerWidth` parameter (already available at call site)
- Build plain text cell values from structured data (headers + rows)
- Measure natural column widths using `stringWidth` (already imported)
- Shrink columns proportionally if total exceeds `innerWidth`
- Right-align numeric columns (detect via checking if all row values for a column are numbers)
- Render each row as space-padded columns with a 2-char gap
- Add a thin separator line (`─`) between header and data
- Style header with `chalk.bold()` and separator with `muted()` in non-plain mode

New implementation:

```typescript
const TABLE_COL_GAP = 2;

function renderTableContent(data: TableResult, innerWidth: number): string[] {
  if (data.rows.length === 0) {
    return [noDataLine()];
  }

  const plain = isPlainOutput();
  const headers = data.columns.map((c) => c.name.toUpperCase());

  // Build plain text cell values
  const cellRows: string[][] = data.rows.map((row) =>
    data.columns.map((col) => {
      const val = row[col.name];
      if (val === null || val === undefined) return "";
      if (typeof val === "number") return formatWithUnit(val, col.unit);
      return String(val);
    })
  );

  // Detect right-aligned (numeric) columns
  const rightAlign = data.columns.map((col, _i) =>
    cellRows.length > 0 &&
    cellRows.every((row, ri) => {
      const v = row[_i] ?? "";
      return v === "" || typeof data.rows[ri]?.[col.name] === "number";
    })
  );

  // Measure natural column widths
  const colWidths = headers.map((h, i) => {
    let maxW = stringWidth(h);
    for (const row of cellRows) {
      maxW = Math.max(maxW, stringWidth(row[i] ?? ""));
    }
    return maxW;
  });

  // Shrink columns proportionally if total exceeds innerWidth
  const totalGap = TABLE_COL_GAP * Math.max(0, colWidths.length - 1);
  const totalNatural = colWidths.reduce((s, w) => s + w, 0) + totalGap;
  if (totalNatural > innerWidth && colWidths.length > 0) {
    const available = Math.max(colWidths.length * 3, innerWidth - totalGap);
    const scale = available / colWidths.reduce((s, w) => s + w, 0);
    for (let i = 0; i < colWidths.length; i++) {
      colWidths[i] = Math.max(3, Math.floor((colWidths[i] ?? 0) * scale));
    }
  }

  const gap = " ".repeat(TABLE_COL_GAP);

  /** Fit a cell to column width, padding or truncating with "…" */
  const fitCell = (text: string, width: number, right: boolean): string => {
    const w = stringWidth(text);
    if (w <= width) {
      const pad = " ".repeat(width - w);
      return right ? pad + text : text + pad;
    }
    // Truncate: walk chars, append "…"
    let result = "";
    let used = 0;
    for (const ch of text) {
      const cw = stringWidth(ch);
      if (used + cw + 1 > width) break;
      result += ch;
      used += cw;
    }
    result += "\u2026";
    used = stringWidth(result);
    const remaining = Math.max(0, width - used);
    return right ? " ".repeat(remaining) + result : result + " ".repeat(remaining);
  };

  const headerLine = headers
    .map((h, i) => fitCell(h, colWidths[i] ?? 3, false))
    .join(gap);

  const sepLine = colWidths.map((w) => "\u2500".repeat(w)).join(gap);

  const dataLines = cellRows.map((row) =>
    row
      .map((cell, i) => fitCell(cell, colWidths[i] ?? 3, rightAlign[i] ?? false))
      .join(gap)
  );

  return [
    plain ? headerLine : chalk.bold(headerLine),
    plain ? sepLine : muted(sepLine),
    ...dataLines,
  ];
}
```

### 2. Update call site (dashboard.ts:1428-1429)

Pass `innerWidth` to `renderTableContent`:

```typescript
// Before:
case "table":
  return renderTableContent(data);

// After:
case "table":
  return renderTableContent(data, innerWidth);
```

### 3. Remove unused imports (dashboard.ts:22)

```typescript
// Before:
import { escapeMarkdownCell, mdRow, mdTableHeader } from "./markdown.js";

// After: Remove this entire import line (nothing else in the file uses these)
```

