- Run `bun test test/lib/formatters/dashboard.test.ts` — existing tests check for content presence (headers, cell values) and should pass without changes
- Run `bun run typecheck` to verify no type errors
- Run `bun run lint` to check for style issues

# Fix: timeseries bar charts cut off last bars

## Problem

The last 2+ bars of every timeseries bar chart are missing. Root cause: `Math.floor(chartWidth / sampled.length)` truncates `barWidth`, so `barWidth * sampled.length < chartWidth`. The bars collectively don't fill the chart area, but the X-axis extends the full width, making the right side look empty.

**File**: `src/lib/formatters/dashboard.ts`

## Fix: distribute remainder across bars (Bresenham-style)

### 1. Single-series bars (`renderTimeBarRows`, lines 1224-1243)

Compute `remainder = chartWidth - barWidth * sampled.length`. The first `remainder` bars get width `barWidth + 1`, the rest get `barWidth`.

```typescript
// Line 1228, after barWidth:
const remainder = chartWidth - barWidth * sampled.length;

// Line 1240-1241, change:
const parts = heights.map((h) =>
  colorFn(buildTimeseriesBarColumn(h, row).repeat(barWidth))
);
// To:
const parts = heights.map((h, col) => {
  const w = barWidth + (col < remainder ? 1 : 0);
  return colorFn(buildTimeseriesBarColumn(h, row).repeat(w));
});
```

### 2. Stacked bars (`renderStackedTimeBarRows`, lines 1316-1364)

Same pattern — compute remainder after `barWidth`, pass per-column width to `buildStackedColumn`.

```typescript
// Line 1320, after barWidth:
const remainder = chartWidth - barWidth * numBuckets;

// Line 1355-1362, change buildStackedColumn call:
const w = barWidth + (col < remainder ? 1 : 0);
const ch = buildStackedColumn(stackedHeights[col] ?? [], row, plain, w);
```

### 3. Check `buildStackedColumn` signature

Verify it already accepts `barWidth` as a parameter — it does (line ~1370), so passing `w` instead works directly.

## Verify

- `bun test test/lib/formatters/dashboard.test.ts`
- `bun run typecheck`
- Visual: `bun dev dashboard view CLI -t 24h` — bars should fill to the right edge
